    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-20T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="1221"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1221">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.504/7–2044: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-20T11:00:00-06:00"
                            >July 20, 1944—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 22—8 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–2525. The Ministry of Labor has announced that an accord has been signed among
                    the Syndicate of Railway Workers of the Mexican Republic, the Brotherhood of
                    Mexican Railway Trainmen, and the Mexican Union of Brother Boilermakers, Helpers
                    and the like.</p>
                <p>The disputes and quarrels among these railway unions are considered one of the
                    reasons for the inefficient operation of the railways and this accord may have
                    an important bearing on the improvement of railway transportation which is
                    virtually the key to the economic crisis in Mexico.</p>
                <p>The full text and translation of the accord will be forwarded to the Department
                    by airmail.<note n="12" xml:id="d1221fn12">Forwarded in despatch 18839 of July
                        19, 1944, not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Messersmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
